article.description: Danielle McCray and Krysten Boogaard combined for 49 points to lead Kansas to a 75-72 victory over Illinois State in a WNIT semifinal on Wednesday.
article.headline: McCray scores 31 to lead Kansas over Illinois State
article.linkText: Kansas holds off Illinois State for WNIT title bid
article.story:
LAWRENCE, Kan. -- Danielle McCray and Krysten Boogaard combined for 49 points to lead Kansas to a 75-72 victory over Illinois State in a WNIT semifinal on Wednesday.

In what was a back-and-forth battle with three ties and nine lead changes, the Jayhawks stopped  a second-half rally by Illinois State to advance to the championship game, where they will face South Florida on Saturday at Allen Fieldhouse.

McCray had 31 points and six rebounds. Boogaard finished with 18 points, seven rebounds and three blocks.  

McCray and Nicollette Smith hit free throws down the stretch to help seal the victory for the Jayhawks.  Illinois State closed to within 61-59 with 3:35 to go on two free throws by Nicolle Lewis.  But the Jayhawks made 10-of-11 free throws in the closing minutes. Smith made 7 of 8.
